# Vercel Web Analytics Integration for Vue 2

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Vue 2 project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version 1.6.1 to dependencies using pnpm
- Created `pnpm-lock.yaml` to lock dependencies

### 2. Updated src/App.vue
- Imported the `inject` function from `@vercel/analytics`
- Added a `created()` lifecycle hook to initialize Web Analytics
- Used the `inject()` approach instead of the `<Analytics />` component because:
  - This is a Vue 2 project (v2.6.14)
  - The Analytics component uses Vue 3 Composition API features (like `useRoute()`)
  - The `inject()` function works universally across all frameworks and Vue versions

### Configuration Details
The analytics are initialized with:
- `mode: 'auto'` - Automatically detects the environment (development/production)
- `framework: 'vue'` - Identifies the framework for Vercel's tracking
- Auto-tracking is enabled by default, which means page views are automatically tracked when the router changes

## Implementation Notes

### Vue 2 Compatibility
While `@vercel/analytics` officially targets Vue 3, the generic `inject()` function works perfectly with Vue 2. The inject function:
- Adds the analytics script to the page head
- Automatically tracks page views when using vue-router
- Respects development vs production environments
- Works with the existing Vercel Speed Insights already in the project

### Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `src/App.vue` - Added analytics initialization in the created hook
- `pnpm-lock.yaml` - New file to lock dependencies

## Testing
✅ Build completed successfully (no errors)
✅ Linter passed with no errors
✅ No breaking changes to existing functionality
✅ Analytics will activate automatically when deployed to Vercel

## Next Steps
Once deployed to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in your Vercel project settings
2. Analytics will start collecting data automatically
3. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab
